  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT260-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">avar varaviṟku nimittam āyiṉa kaṇṭu āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaṭkut tōḻi
          colliyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante speaking to HER who didn't have strength
          [anymore], upon seeing the signs for his coming. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT260">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l>kuruku miruvicum pivarum putalum</l>
          <l>varivaṇ ṭūta vāynekiḻn taṉavē</l>
          <l>curivaḷaip polinta tōḷuñ ceṟṟum</l>
          <l>varuvarkol vāḻi tōḻi poruvār</l>
          <l>maṇṇeṭut tuṇṇu maṇṇal yāṉai</l>
          <l>vaṇṭērt toṇṭaiyar vaḻaiyama laṭukkattuk</l>
          <l>kaṉṟi lōrā vilaṅkiya</l>
          <l>puṉṟā ḷōmaiya curaṉiṟan tōrē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Herons are climbing the dark sky, and shrubs</l>
          <l>have opened [their blossom] mouths</l>
          <l rend="indent6">so that striped bees fill themselves [with pollen]. </l>
          <l rend="indent">Even though [my] upper arms glittering with winding bangles</l>
          <l rend="indent9">have resisted, </l>
          <l>will he come, oh friend,</l>
          <l>he who traversed the desert of low-based Ōmai trees,</l>
          <l rend="indent">across which lies a single cow without calf</l>
          <l rend="indent2">from the mountainside thick with Vaḻai trees,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">of the Toṇṭaiyar with many chariots [and] majestic elephants, </l>
          <l>who take over the land of [enemy] fighters? </l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="7b" resp="#TVG">
            <l>which prevented a calfless cow [from going further]</l>
          </lg>

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
